\[
\mathrm P\left\{|u(t,0)-1|\le |\sigma(1)|\,\theta\, t^{1/4}\ \text{for all }t\in[\varepsilon f(\varepsilon),\varepsilon]\right\}
=f(\varepsilon)^{\lambda(\theta)+o(1)}
\]
holds for every \(\theta>0\) and every function \(f:(0,1/e)\to(0,1/e)\) with \(f(\varepsilon)\to0\) as \(\varepsilon\to0^+\), even without assuming \(f(\varepsilon)\ge \varepsilon^{\ell+o(1)}\).
